lause was found prohibiting use of personal information outside the specific business purpose.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"§ 1798.140(ag)(1)(B) requires the contract to prohibit the service provider from retaining, using, or disclosing personal information for any purpose other than the specific business purpose enumerated.","id":"USDPA-001-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Service Provider shall not retain, use, or disclose personal information for any purpose other than the specific business purpose enumerated in this Agreement.'","rule_id":"USDPA-001","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-civ-code-1798-140-ag-1-b-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.140(ag)(1)(B)","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"CCPA purpose-limitation clause missing"},{"description":"No clause was found prohibiting sale of personal information.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"§ 1798.140(ag)(1)(A) requires a no-sale prohibition.","id":"USDPA-002-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Service Provider is prohibited from selling personal information.'","rule_id":"USDPA-002","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-civ-code-1798-140-ag-1-a-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.140(ag)(1)(A)","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"CCPA no-sale prohibition missing"},{"description":"No clause was found requiring the same level of privacy protection.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"§ 1798.100(d) requires the contract to obligate the third party / service provider to comply with applicable obligations and provide the same level of privacy protection as required by the CCPA.","id":"USDPA-005-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Service Provider shall comply with all applicable obligations under the CCPA and provide the same level of privacy protection as required by the CCPA.'","rule_id":"USDPA-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-civ-code-1798-100-d-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.100(d)","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"CCPA same-level-of-protection clause missing"},{"description":"No clause was found granting the business reasonable monitoring / oversight rights.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"§ 1798.140(ag)(1)(C) requires the contract to grant the business the right to take reasonable and appropriate steps to ensure that the service provider uses the personal information in a manner consistent with the business's obligations under the CCPA.","id":"USDPA-007-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Business may take reasonable and appropriate steps to ensure that Service Provider uses personal information in a manner consistent with Business's obligations under the CCPA.'","rule_id":"USDPA-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-civ-code-1798-140-ag-1-c-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.140(ag)(1)(C)","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"CCPA monitoring right missing"},{"description":"No clause was found requiring notification if service provider can no longer meet CCPA obligations.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"§ 7051(a)(6) requires the service provider to notify the business if it makes a determination that it can no longer meet its obligations under the CCPA.","id":"USDPA-009-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Service Provider shall notify Business if it makes a determination that it can no longer meet its obligations under the CCPA.'","rule_id":"USDPA-009","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-code-regs-tit-11-7051-a-6-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Code Regs. tit. 11, § 7051(a)(6)","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"CCPA inability-to-comply notification missing"},{"description":"No clause was found stating the nature and purpose of processing.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"VCDPA, CPA, CTDPA, UCPA, TDPSA, OCPA, DPDPA all require the contract to state the nature and purpose of processing.","id":"USDPA-012-s1-0","recommendation":"Add a 'Nature and Purpose of Processing' clause.","rule_id":"USDPA-012","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-va-code-59-1-579-colo-rev-stat-6-1-1305-similar","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Va. Code § 59.1-579 / Colo. Rev. Stat. § 6-1-1305 / similar","source_url":"https://law.lis.virginia.gov/vacodefull/title59.1/chapter53/"}],"title":"Nature-and-purpose clause missing"},{"description":"No clause was found identifying the type of personal data.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Each state requires the contract to specify the categories of personal data.","id":"USDPA-013-s1-0","recommendation":"Add an Annex listing the categories of personal data processed.","rule_id":"USDPA-013","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-va-code-59-1-579-colo-rev-stat-6-1-1305-similar","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Va. Code § 59.1-579 / Colo. Rev. Stat. § 6-1-1305 / similar","source_url":"https://law.lis.virginia.gov/vacodefull/title59.1/chapter53/"}],"title":"Type-of-data clause missing"},{"description":"No clause was found stating the duration of processing.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Every state's processor-contract statute requires the duration to be set out.","id":"USDPA-014-s1-0","recommendation":"State that processing continues for the term of the agreement.","rule_id":"USDPA-014","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-va-code-59-1-579-colo-rev-stat-6-1-1305-similar","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Va. Code § 59.1-579 / Colo. Rev. Stat. § 6-1-1305 / similar","source_url":"https://law.lis.virginia.gov/vacodefull/title59.1/chapter53/"}],"title":"Duration-of-processing clause missing"},{"description":"No clause was found obligating the processor to cooperate with reasonable assessments.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"VCDPA and several state statutes require the processor to allow and cooperate with reasonable assessments by the controller.","id":"USDPA-017-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Processor shall allow and cooperate with reasonable assessments by Controller or Controller's designated assessor.'","rule_id":"USDPA-017","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"critical","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-va-code-59-1-579-colo-rev-stat-6-1-1305-similar","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Va. Code § 59.1-579 / Colo. Rev. Stat. § 6-1-1305 / similar","source_url":"https://law.lis.virginia.gov/vacodefull/title59.1/chapter53/"}],"title":"Audit cooperation clause missing"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a governing-law clause.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no governing-law clause)"},"explanation":"A governing-law clause picks the legal system that interprets the contract. Without it, courts apply conflict-of-laws rules, which may produce unexpected results.","id":"CHOICE-001-s1-0","rule_id":"CHOICE-001","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No governing-law clause detected"},{"description":"The contract does not allocate ownership of intellectual property.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no IP-ownership clause)"},"explanation":"Without an IP-ownership clause, default copyright and patent rules apply: under 17 U.S.C. § 201, copyright vests in the author/employee unless work-for-hire or assignment applies.","id":"IPDATA-001-s1-0","rule_id":"IPDATA-001","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-17-usc-101","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 101 — Definitions (work made for hire)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/101"},{"id":"stat-17-usc-201","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 201","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/201"}],"title":"No IP-ownership clause detected"},{"description":"Neither 'indemnify' nor 'hold harmless' appears in the document.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no indemnification language)"},"explanation":"Most commercial contracts allocate risk through an indemnification clause. The absence leaves the parties to default tort and contract law for any third-party claims.","id":"RISK-001-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-001","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No indemnification clause detected"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a limitation-of-liability clause.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no LoL clause)"},"explanation":"Without a limitation-of-liability clause, exposure is bounded only by what the parties can prove in damages. Most commercial contracts cap liability.","id":"RISK-005-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No limitation-of-liability clause detected"},{"description":"Used but not defined: Applicable State Law, Business Purpose, Utah Code.","document_position":3401,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3421,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":3401,"text":"Applicable State Law"},"explanation":"Title-Case phrases in a contract usually signal a defined term. When they aren't defined, readers must guess at the intended meaning. Either define them or use lowercase if the term is intended in its ordinary sense.","id":"STRUCT-006-s1-3401","recommendation":"Add a definition for each genuinely defined term, or change the casing if the phrase is being used in its ordinary sense.","rule_id":"STRUCT-006","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"Undefined Title-Case terms: 3"},{"description":"The contract does not state a path to terminate for material breach.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no for-cause termination)"},"explanation":"Without a for-cause termination path, parties must rely on common-law material-breach doctrines, which are jurisdiction-dependent.","id":"TERM-002-s1-0","rule_id":"TERM-002","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No termination-for-cause clause detected"},{"description":"The contract does not state what happens upon termination.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no effect-of-termination clause)"},"explanation":"An effect-of-termination clause spells out the rights and obligations that survive, the return or destruction of materials, and the wind-down rules.","id":"TERM-005-s1-0","rule_id":"TERM-005","rule_version":"1.2.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No effect-of-termination clause detected"},{"description":"No service-provider certification of CCPA understanding was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"§ 7051(a)(7) expects the contract to require service-provider certification that it understands the restrictions and will comply.","id":"USDPA-006-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Service Provider certifies that it understands the restrictions in this Agreement and the CCPA and will comply with them.'","rule_id":"USDPA-006","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-code-regs-tit-11-7051-a-7-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Code Regs. tit. 11, § 7051(a)(7)","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"CCPA certification of understanding missing"},{"description":"No clause was found specifically addressing sensitive personal information.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"CCPA / CPRA, CPA, CTDPA define sensitive personal information / sensitive data and impose heightened obligations.","id":"USDPA-022-s1-0","recommendation":"Add a 'Sensitive Personal Information' clause describing categories handled and SPI-specific safeguards.","rule_id":"USDPA-022","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-civ-code-1798-121","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.121","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"Sensitive personal information handling not addressed"},{"description":"No reference to data minimization was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Several state privacy statutes incorporate a data-minimization principle requiring collection of only what is reasonably necessary.","id":"USDPA-024-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Personal data collected and processed shall be limited to what is reasonably necessary and proportionate to the disclosed purpose.'","rule_id":"USDPA-024","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-cal-civ-code-1798-100-c-multi-state-minimization","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.100(c) / Multi-state minimization","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"Data-minimization principle not referenced"},{"description":"The document does not state where disputes must be brought.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no venue clause)"},"explanation":"Without a venue clause, default venue rules apply (in federal court, 28 U.S.C. § 1391). A clear forum-selection clause avoids ambiguity.","id":"CHOICE-003-s1-0","rule_id":"CHOICE-003","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-28-usc-1391","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"28 U.S.C. § 1391 (venue generally)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/28/1391"}],"title":"No venue / forum clause detected"},{"description":"Service Provider shall not: (a) sell personal information as defined in Cal. | § 6-1-1305(5), Service Provider shall implement and maintain appropriate technical and organizational measures to protec","document_position":1283,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1360,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1283,"text":"Service Provider shall not: (a) sell personal information as defined in Cal."},"explanation":"Negative covenants restrict what a party may do. Surfacing them collectively makes it easier to check they are intended and consistent with the overall deal.","id":"OBLI-005-s1-1283","rule_id":"OBLI-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Negative covenants: 2"},{"description":"Detected a multi-state DPA using minimum 'Utah-style' contract terms where stricter state law (CCPA, CPA, CTDPA) may apply.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":11,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"Multi-State US Data Processing Addendum"},"explanation":"When a contract spans multiple states, the strictest applicable requirement should govern. Using minimum-common-denominator language risks non-compliance with the stricter states.","id":"USDPA-021-s1-0","recommendation":"Adopt the strictest applicable state's required elements (typically CCPA / CPA / CTDPA) and document the multi-state coverage explicitly.","rule_id":"USDPA-021","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"us-state-multi-state-dpa-compliance","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"Multi-state DPA compliance","source_url":"https://oag.ca.gov/privacy/ccpa"}],"title":"Multi-state contract may not meet strictest applicable requirement"}],"playbook_id":"dpa-multi-state-us","playbook_match_confidence":1,"playbook_match_reasoning":"forced via sidecar to dpa-multi-state-us","result_hash":"3826062f107040508b0d76bbe72604dd78e7fdcd5033138089c1a8c5e2882384","source_file":{"name":"dpa-multi-state-us-minimal-pass.txt","sha256":"6b74c75756d70ae24669a5f44fcdbd19d8b0d7a9b04998420124ec21808ed85c","size_bytes":1},"version":"9.41.0"}